<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="394" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1646,1926]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1862,1888]" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Distribution.</emphasis>
Mountains of Central Asia and Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[837,971,1863,1889]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, Southern Siberia eastwards up to Tyva, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,263,1899,1925]" name="Mongolia" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[322,389,1899,1925]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[403,508,1899,1926]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
). In Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[708,839,1899,1925]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="13" pageNumber="394">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
was found only on Dzhungarsky Alatau Range.
</paragraph>
